<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!-- 
 To create a new language type:
 1. copy the <language>..</language> block, rename the name attribute
 2. customize the fileType/extension, quotation, escape, changeLine,
    ..., especially, the singleLineComment and blockComment marks.
    multiple marks/names may be defined for:
    - file extension list (extension must be separated by ";", start with ".")
    - quotation mark (optional)
    - single-line comment mark (optional, if really does not exist)
    - block comment mark (optional, if really does not exist)
    multiple marks MAY NOT be defined for:
    - escape mark (optional; one character)
    - noescape mark (optional; one character)
    - changeline mark (optional; one character)
 3. parsing error of config.xml will be output to the log file
 4. Escape Symbol of this xml config file:
    (If you want to use these symbols for e.g. xml file's mark, use the escape symbols)
	   &     : &#38;  or  &amp;
	   <     : &#60;  or  &lt;
	   >     : &#62;  or  &gt;
 5. Finally, create a new projectType under the <projectTypeList>, 
    specified relative fileTypes.
 -->
